lines.text: And do you know what we do with shit around here, Nick?
From your breath, I'd say you eat it.
You're a cop?
Surprise, surprise.
You're a teacher?
Surprise, surprise.
You're a cop?
Surprise, surprise.
Gee, Kyle, is this really fair? There are only three of you!
[two more Wardens appear]
Ah. That's more like it.
You're supposed to be helping your brother Matt, not getting nippy with some cheerleaders!
Tonight's the night, Nick.
Gee, that sounds really romantic, Kyle, but right now I can't.
I knew it! I knew he was too polite to be a student!
Will somebody please tell me what the hell's going on?
Gee, it's your case, Dave.
They actually put cops on stuff like this?
Tell me about it.
Dunbar, get me a cup of coffee, two sugars.
Yes, sir.
Easy to see who has all the status around here, Dunbar.
Just pretend to be a student - you're supposed to be good at that kind of thing.
Matt, no one is going to believe I am a high school kid.
Nick, be serious - no one believes you're a cop!
